      "content": "High volume is fine, but it doesn't explain why I'd cut my price when your factory is supposedly running low. If you're facing a shortage, you're a buyer in a position of weakness, not strength. You should be begging for the stock, not asking for a discount. Tell me exactly what's going on on your end that makes a lower price make sense for a rush order.",
